Package de.yamass.redg.generator.extractor.datatypeprovider.xml

Class XmlFileDataTypeProvider

java.lang.Object
de.yamass.redg.generator.extractor.datatypeprovider.xml.XmlFileDataTypeProvider
All Implemented Interfaces:
DataTypeProvider
public class XmlFileDataTypeProvider extends Object implements DataTypeProvider

A data type provider that reads the types from a json file.

The format for the file is: 

 <typeMappings>
   <tableTypeMappings>
     <table tableName="CUSTOMER">
       <column columnName="DTYPE" javaType="example.CustomerType"/>
     </table>
   </tableTypeMappings>
   <defaultTypeMappings>
     <typeMapping sqlType="TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE" javaType="java.sql.Timestamp"/>
   </defaultTypeMappings>
 </typeMappings>

    • getCanonicalDataTypeName

      public String getCanonicalDataTypeName(schemacrawler.schema.Column column)
      Description copied from interface: DataTypeProvider
      Called by during the model data extraction process for each column that is being processed with the current column as the parameter. This method has to decide on the data type that will later represent this column in the generated java code.

      Information about the Table can be obtained by calling ContainedObject.getParent().

      Information about the SQL Data type and what schemacrawler recommends can be obtained by calling BaseColumn.getColumnDataType().

      Specified by:
      getCanonicalDataTypeName in interface DataTypeProvider
      Parameters:
      column - The current column
      Returns:
      The canonical name of the data type to use for the given column
